        • suspendResumeEntities

          boolean suspendResumeEntities
          This parameter defines whether the agent whose task is suspended
          should be automatically suspended in its current flowchart block
          and automatically resumed at the time there are available resources.
          Suspend occurs because of SEIZE_ANY_RESOURCE and WAIT_FOR_ORIGINAL_RESOURCE
          preemption policy, when the resource unit owned by the agent gets grabbed by
          another task with higher priority.

          There are callbacks: "On task suspended", it is executed after auto-suspend,
          and "On task resumed", it is executed before auto-resume

        • queuing

          Queue.QueuingMode queuing
          Defines priorities for agents placement in the queue:
          - QUEUING_FIFO - (first in - first out) an ordinary queue
          - QUEUING_PRIORITY - agents are placed according to the 'priority' numeric value
          - QUEUING_COMPARISON - each incoming agent is compared to other agents (in terms of question 'is this agent more privileged than ...?')
          - QUEUING_LIFO - (last in - first out) the most recent incoming agent will be the first to exit

          If queue gets full and preemption is 'on', any further incoming agent from PUSH-enabled block (port) makes queue to push out some agent which has the least priority according to the selected mode. In FIFO mode, full queue simply redirects further incoming agents straight to 'outPreempted' port.

        • queuing

          Queue.QueuingMode queuing
          Defines priorities for agents placement in the queue:
          - QUEUING_FIFO - (first in - first out) an ordinary queue
          - QUEUING_PRIORITY - agents are placed according to the 'priority' numeric value
          - QUEUING_COMPARISON - each incoming agent is compared to other agents (in terms of question 'is this agent more privileged than ...?')
          - QUEUING_LIFO - (last in - first out) the most recent incoming agent will be the first to exit

          If queue gets full and preemption is 'on', any further incoming agent from PUSH-enabled block (port) makes queue to push out some agent which has the least priority according to the selected mode. In FIFO mode, full queue simply redirects further incoming agents straight to 'outPreempted' port.
